    "content": "<div id=\"core\" align=\"center\"><picture><source media=\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\" srcset=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/yummyfiles/MusicX/main/MusicX/banner.svg\"><img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/yummyfiles/MusicX/main/MusicX/banner.svg\" alt=\"MusicX\" width=\"100%\" /></picture><br><a href=\"https://github.com/yummyfiles/MusicX/releases/latest\"><picture><source media=\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\" srcset=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/DOWNLOAD_APK-000000?style=for-the-badge&logo=android&logoColor=white&labelColor=000000&color=000000\"><img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/DOWNLOAD_APK-ffffff?style=for-the-badge&logo=android&logoColor=000000&labelColor=ffffff&color=ffffff\" alt=\"Download APK\" /></picture></a><br><br><p>No ads. No subscriptions. No accounts.<br>No Start Free Trial button stalking you.</p></div><hr><div id=\"why\"><h2>Why I Built This</h2><p>Most music apps are doing the absolute most.</p><p>Ads.<br>Premium popups.<br>Sign in to continue.<br>Upgrade to unlock basic functionality.</p><p>I just wanted to press play and hear music.</p><p>So I made MusicX.</p><p>It opens.<br>It scans your songs.<br>It plays them.</p></div><hr><div id=\"features\"><h2>What You Get</h2><ul><li>Fully offline playback</li><li>Local music scanning</li><li>Fast search for songs, artists, and metadata</li><li>Playlist support</li><li>Lyrics support through embedded lyrics and LRCLIB</li><li>Background playback</li><li>Lock screen and notification controls</li><li>Clean, minimal UI</li><li>Advanced color customization</li></ul><p>No streaming.<br>No cloud.<br>No tracking.<br>No account creation side quest.</p></div><hr><div id=\"customization\"><h2>Customization</h2><p>You can tweak pretty much every color in the app — backgrounds, text, accents, player UI, buttons, and more.</p><p>If you want your music player pure black and minimal, you can.</p><p>If you want it looking like a neon science experiment, you can also do that.</p></div><hr><div id=\"how\"><h2>How It Works</h2><ul><li>Scans your music using Android MediaStore</li><li>Everything stays on your device</li><li>Built with Kotlin and Jetpack Compose</li><li>Uses Media3 / ExoPlayer for playback</li></ul></div><hr><div id=\"faq\"><h2>FAQ</h2><p><strong>Does it stream music?</strong><br>No. Local files only.</p><p><strong>Does it need internet?</strong><br>Nope.</p><p><strong>Are there ads?</strong><br>Never.</p><p><strong>Do I need an account?</strong><br>Absolutely not.</p><p><strong>Is my music uploaded anywhere?</strong><br>No. It stays on your device.</p></div><hr><div id=\"goal\"><h2>The Goal</h2><p>Open app, pick song, play music.</p><p>That's it.</p><p>No popups.<br>No paywalls.<br>No emotional manipulation to buy premium.</p></div>"
